## Finding: No Alpha Exit Criteria or Graduation Checklist

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: The qa_playbook has an exit checklist for QA test runs, but there is no skill defining what signals graduate the product from alpha to beta. World-class software programs define alpha exit criteria such as: crash-free session rate > X%, median response time < Y ms, feedback sentiment score > Z, N active testers completing core flows, zero P0 open bugs, backup restore verified, all checklist items green. Without defined exit criteria, alpha-to-beta transition is subjective and likely premature.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill or section within an alpha_program_management skill: alpha_exit_criteria — defines quantitative graduation gates, a dashboard template for tracking gate status, and an explicit sign-off process.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Directly gates Phase 5.75 entry. Beta with premature alpha graduation risks exposing a larger audience to unresolved alpha-phase issues.

