## Finding: backup_strategy Depth Grade — ADEQUATE (not thorough for alpha context)

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: The backup_strategy skill is thorough for general PostgreSQL backup mechanics (pg_dump, S3 upload, retention, restore verification, encryption). However, it is shallow in two alpha-specific dimensions: (1) It does not address backup cadence calibration during alpha — alpha databases are small but rapidly changing as schema migrations occur frequently; the skill's "daily backup" default may be insufficient and "pre-migration backup" is mentioned but not enforced as a gate in the alpha CI pipeline. (2) It has no guidance on communicating data durability guarantees to alpha testers — testers need to know if their alpha data will survive to beta or be wiped. The skill's GDPR export script is included which is appropriate, but there is no alpha-specific data lifecycle policy (e.g., "alpha data is ephemeral unless we announce GA data portability").
### Proposed Resolution: Add an alpha-context section to backup_strategy covering: alpha data lifecycle policy template, pre-migration backup as a mandatory CI gate (not optional), communication template for tester data expectations.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.75 Beta testers may be surprised if alpha data is wiped. Without a communicated policy, this creates trust damage with the cohort that is your most influential early adopters.

