## Finding: health_checks Depth Grade — ADEQUATE (missing synthetic monitoring)

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: health_checks covers NestJS Terminus, liveness/readiness/detailed endpoints, custom DB and Redis indicators, Kubernetes probes, and external uptime monitoring setup. Good coverage. Missing: (1) Synthetic transaction monitoring — health checks verify the API is up, but do not verify that a real user flow works end-to-end. During alpha, a broken checkout or login that still returns 200 on /health/ready goes undetected. (2) No SLA definition — the skill tells you to monitor but does not guide you to define what "acceptable uptime" means for alpha (99%? 95%? No SLA?). (3) The detailed endpoint returns memory/disk metrics but there is no guidance on what thresholds to set as alerts — teams will set up the endpoint and then have no idea what numbers are bad.
### Proposed Resolution: Add synthetic monitoring section (Checkly or Playwright-based smoke tests on a schedule), SLA definition guidance for alpha context, and alert threshold decision matrix.
