### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: qa_playbook is a well-structured manual testing framework. However, it is written for general use — the test cases (Auth, CRUD, Errors, Performance, Security, SaaS-specific) are generic. For an alpha program, it is missing: (1) Alpha-specific test scenarios — onboarding flow for a new invited tester, invite code redemption, alpha cohort data isolation verification, alpha feature flag activation. (2) No exploratory testing program for alpha — during alpha, you should be doing structured exploratory testing sessions with actual alpha testers (not just internal QA), including guided walkthroughs and think-aloud protocols. (3) No alpha tester-reported bug triage workflow — the bug severity classification is good, but there is no process for when alpha testers (not internal QA) submit bugs through a feedback channel. (4) The regression checklist is 5-minute post-deploy — good, but alpha also needs a weekly "alpha health review" checklist covering cohort activity rates, Sentry error trends, and backup verification status.
