## Finding: Phase 5.5 Assumes Crash Reporting Exists But Telemetry Backpressure Is Unaddressed

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: error_tracking sets up Sentry with tracesSampleRate=0.2 in production (and by inheritance, alpha). If alpha traffic spikes unexpectedly (a tester shares an invite link, cohort doubles overnight), Sentry event volume could spike and hit free-tier rate limits, causing error events to be dropped precisely when you need them most. There is no skill in Phase 5.5 covering telemetry backpressure: Sentry rate limit monitoring, event sampling strategy under load, fallback logging when Sentry is rate-limited. This is an alpha-specific risk because the team has no historical baseline to set quotas from.
