## Finding: Reverse-Think — Alpha Data Loss Prevention Is Completely Absent

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Working backward from a perfect alpha completion: "If this alpha succeeded, the team had zero data loss events that affected tester trust." For this to be true, the following must have existed: (1) A documented data durability promise communicated to alpha testers at onboarding ("your data will be preserved through beta"). (2) A pre-migration backup gate in CI that is enforced, not optional. (3) A soft-delete pattern or recycle bin for critical entities that alpha testers might accidentally delete. (4) A data recovery SLA communicated to testers ("if data loss occurs, we will restore within X hours"). The backup_strategy skill covers the technical backup mechanics but none of these trust/communication/policy dimensions. The end-state of "testers trust their data" requires all four elements, and three of them are entirely absent from the framework.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill: alpha_data_policy — covers the data durability promise document, soft-delete implementation pattern, data recovery SLA definition, and the pre-migration backup CI gate as a required step (not optional).
### Cross-Phase Impact: Tester data trust established in alpha is the foundation for paying customer data trust in beta. Teams that lose alpha tester data typically see abandonment from their most vocal early adopters.

================================================================

## Finding: Reverse-Think — Session Recording and Crash Reporting Are Shallow

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Working backward from "the team understood exactly what alpha testers experienced when things broke." For this to be true: session replays tied to specific error events must exist, crash reports must include enough context (user actions leading up to crash, network conditions, device specs) to reproduce the issue. The error_tracking skill configures Sentry Session Replay with maskAllText: true and blockAllMedia: true — these privacy defaults are appropriate for production but are overly restrictive for alpha where testers have explicitly consented to being observed. The skill does not provide: (1) guidance on alpha-specific replay configuration with reduced masking, (2) Sentry Feedback widget configuration (Sentry's built-in feedback capture on error), (3) custom breadcrumb instrumentation to capture the specific user actions that preceded each crash.
### Proposed Resolution: Extend error_tracking with an alpha-specific session recording section: conditional replay configuration based on NODE_ENV/ALPHA_MODE, Sentry Feedback widget setup, and a custom breadcrumbs guide for instrumenting critical user flows.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Detailed crash context from alpha is what allows rapid bug fixing before beta. Without it, beta launches with the same undiagnosed bugs.

