## Finding: Spec — alpha_exit_criteria Skill

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Confirmed by Loop 1 (no graduation checklist), Loop 4 (reverse-think on structured program completion).
### Proposed Resolution:
**Skill Name**: alpha_exit_criteria
**Phase**: 5.5-alpha
**Trigger Commands**:
- "define alpha exit criteria"
- "alpha graduation requirements"
- "ready for beta"
- "alpha to beta checklist"
- "Using alpha_exit_criteria skill: define the gates for graduating to beta"

**Scope**: Defines the quantitative and qualitative gates that must be met before transitioning from alpha to beta. Template covers: (1) Reliability gates: crash-free session rate > 98%, uptime > 99% over trailing 7 days, zero open P0 bugs, all P1 bugs have documented workarounds. (2) Performance gates: p95 response time within baseline range, no memory leak trend in 7-day rolling window, backup restore test passed within last 7 days. (3) Coverage gates: all qa_playbook P0/P1 test cases passing, OWASP ASVS Level 1 checklist complete, env_validation covers all production vars. (4) Tester engagement gates: N% of alpha testers completed core flow at least once, median tester NPS > 6, feedback backlog < X open P1+ issues. (5) Process gates: incident_communication templates tested in a drill, runbook reviewed and signed off, alpha retrospective document drafted. Skill includes a GitHub Issues template for tracking gate status and a sign-off procedure.

**Priority**: P1 — High. The most common alpha failure mode is premature beta launch.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Alpha exit criteria are the direct inputs to Phase 5.75 Beta onboarding. Gates that pass in 5.5 define the minimum quality bar for 5.75.

