## Finding: Dependency Map for All Proposed Skills

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Building on all Loop 7 specs and all earlier findings. The dependency graph between proposed skills and existing skills is as follows:

**Dependency Chain 1 (Critical Path — Alpha Launch Gate)**:
env_validation (existing) → alpha_access_control (new, P0) → alpha_data_policy (new, P0)
The alpha_access_control skill requires new env vars (ALPHA_COHORT_MAX_SIZE, ALPHA_INVITE_SECRET) that must be added to the env_validation schema. alpha_data_policy requires the access control user model to know which records are "tester data."

**Dependency Chain 2 (Observability Stack)**:
error_tracking (existing) → performance_baseline (new, P1) → staged_rollout_verification (new, P1)
performance_baseline depends on error_tracking being configured (Sentry is one instrumentation source). staged_rollout_verification depends on performance_baseline having established the /version endpoint and alpha metrics.

**Dependency Chain 3 (Incident Response)**:
health_checks (existing) → incident_communication (new, P0) → post_incident_review (implicit from Loop 6)
health_checks detects incidents; incident_communication responds to them; post_incident_review learns from them. All three must be in place before alpha goes live.

**Dependency Chain 4 (Alpha Program Graduation)**:
backup_strategy (existing) + qa_playbook (existing) + alpha_exit_criteria (new, P1) → alpha_retrospective (implicit from Loop 3)
alpha_exit_criteria aggregates outputs from backup_strategy (restore test passed), qa_playbook (P0/P1 tests passing), health_checks (uptime %), error_tracking (crash-free sessions), and performance_baseline (latency within baseline). The alpha_retrospective outputs the aggregated state to Phase 5.75.

**Cross-Phase Dependency**:
alpha_access_control (5.5) → feature_flags (5.75) — access control user model is the targeting entity for feature flag rollouts
incident_communication (5.5) → email_templates (5.75) — status page and notification templates established in alpha are extended in beta
performance_baseline (5.5) → product_analytics (5.75) — backend performance baseline feeds into product analytics baseline correlations

### Proposed Resolution: Skills must be implemented in this priority order: (1) alpha_access_control + alpha_data_policy (parallel, both P0, both day-1 alpha requirements), (2) incident_communication (P0, must be ready before any user touches the alpha), (3) performance_baseline (P1, should be running from day 1 of alpha to capture baseline), (4) staged_rollout_verification (P1, needed for first alpha deploy), (5) alpha_exit_criteria (P1, needed before beta transition planning begins).
### Cross-Phase Impact: All proposed skills in Phase 5.5 have direct downstream dependencies in Phase 5.75. None of them are standalone — they are specifically designed to create the foundation that Phase 5.75 builds on.

